Type: Package
Package: gllvmTMB
Title: Fit Multivariate Models from Wide Response Data
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R:
    person("Shinichi", "Nakagawa", , "itchyshin@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-7765-5182"))
Description: Fits multivariate models for data where each site,
    individual, species, or study has several responses. Start from a
    wide data frame with the 'traits()' formula interface, or from
    already-stacked long data, and estimate trait covariance, pairwise
    correlations, shared latent axes, and trait-specific variance.
    Optional animal, phylogenetic, spatial, and known-sampling-variance
    components use the same formula grammar. Model fitting uses
    Template Model Builder (Kristensen et al. 2016
    <doi:10.18637/jss.v070.i05>); spatial helpers inherit from
    'sdmTMB' (Anderson et al. 2025 <doi:10.18637/jss.v115.i02>), and
    phylogenetic relatedness follows Hadfield & Nakagawa (2010)
    <doi:10.1111/j.1420-9101.2009.01915.x>. Upstream copyright holders
    of inherited code are listed in 'inst/COPYRIGHTS'.
